name: Sol Duc Hot Springs Overnight Excursion
description: Hot Springs in our own Olympic National Park!  Join us on the overnight trip for some relaxation and natural hot springs experience.  Take a ferry ride, enjoy trails, hot springs, pools, hike to a waterfall, and just relax.  One night stay accommodation not included. We provide the transportation and connections, you pay for your room/cabin and meals. Book while there's space, we'll help with the arrangements!  Suggest King or queen room with breakfast included:  $245 plus tax while supplies last.

itemListElement.name: Pacific Ocean Experience - Long Beach Peninsula - Private

name: Pacific Ocean Experience - Long Beach Peninsula - Private
description:
Pacific Ocean day excursion, visiting Washington's Long Beach Peninsula.  Plenty of fine light brown sand. Visit a lighthouse, explore the Lewis & Clark Interpretive Center, stop in the Columbia Pacific Heritage Museum. We'll taylor it as we go. Eat some great food, visit a kite museum, stroll the beach, and see what used to be the worlds largest frying pan! 

This is a great day trip from the Seattle area.

itemListElement.name: Canadian Rockies small groups national parks hotel tour 7 days

name: Canadian Rockies small groups national parks hotel tour 7 days
description: Enjoy a fantastic 7 day tour of the Canadian Rocky Mountain national parks. Canoe Lake Louise, explore Banff, Jasper, Yoho national parks and get a glimpse of Mt Robson. Visit Whistler, Vancouver and Clearwater on this tour through Western Canada’s awe-inspiring scenery. Marvel at the stunning scenery, including alpine lakes, waterfalls, giant glaciers and jagged Rocky Mountain’s towering above you at every turn. This tour offers fantastic wildlife spotting opportunities. The maximum group size for this tour is 14 guests.

review.name: Dissatisfying
review.reviewBody: The tour and itinerary were really great. Unfortunately the guides didn't stick to the itinerary and we missed our some places. I felt that the guides saw this tour more as a vacation for themselves and not as a job. Moreover did they choose things they wanted to do and places they wanted to see and we just had to go with it. So we were taken the chance to see Jasper and the and the hot springs. Neither did we visit China Town in Vancouver eventhough we had lots of time on either days the weather was great and we arrived way too early at our hotels. It seemed like the guides skipped those places because THEY didn't want to see it. All over I would say the customer service on this tour was very low since the guides didn't do any effort to make us happy give us different options and I honestly have the feeling they saw it as a vacation for themselves. Since they were into nature and hiking and not into other stuff we skipped some things which in my point of view is a big no go. Besides that I never had the feeling they would care much about the people on the bus and are just interested into the next hiking place they could go .Due to that I would NOT RECOMMEND this company. If you like the itinerary choose another provider . I will NEVER book this company again. I had already lots of tours all over the world but in customer service this one was the worst. Besides that the Clearwater lodge is horrible the ceiling is broken there's stains all over the place furniture /sheets. The entire hotel is in a horrible condition. The Vancouver hotel is right next to a night club so it's super loud all night long. The other accommodations were great. Still over all I am dissatisfied with the tour.

name: Outdoor Trivia Race in Seattle
description: Seattle is being ravaged by a massive outbreak of the "playgue" and only you and your friends can stop it. In this mad dash through Seattle's International District, your team will compete to save as many lives as possible by locating interesting sites, answering bizarre trivia questions, and navigating the most strategic route possible.

name: Skykomish River Whitewater Rafting (Class 4-5)
description: AWESOME! The Sky is the most challenging commercially run whitewater in Washington boasting class 4-5 "Boulder Drop" just 50 miles from downtown Seattle. Technical. Big. Whitewater. This is the one!

review.name: Experts
review.reviewBody: My friends and I had a great time rafting.  Our guides, Ian and Connor, were fun and very experienced.  They made the rafting experience incredible.  They made us feel prepared and made the experience very enjoyable.

review.name: Whitewater Yoga
review.reviewBody: Took my kid rafting with some friends and had a fantastic time. Lauri had a great eye for the river and guided us smoothly through some exciting whitewater. I’d go again tomorrow if I could! Her calm yoga voice kept us all engaged and on task.

review.name: Exciting and fun!
review.reviewBody: Lauri was an amazing guide on our excursion! It was my first time and they made it very accessible and exciting. Will 100% be back again!

review.name: Awesome experience!
review.reviewBody: Duuuuude! Pardon my french but PUTAIN!!!! That was freakin incredible! We went in a group of four with Ian as our guide (and Blake on the other boat) and it was awesome! We didn’t lose a single person overboard- (however the other company lost about 4 people and got stuck pretty bad :/ ) - these guys know what they’re doing. Super friendly and knowledgeable. My girlfriend has gone 5 times already this summer- I’m so glad she introduced us to Triad! Their equipment is all new- wetsuits are clean- they give you great directions- absolutely nothing negative to say!

review.name: Totally Rad
review.reviewBody: Super fun, very expiranced guides. My whole group had a blast! Lori, Blake, Ian, Connor, and all the guides were awesome! I would definitely go again.

review.name: a great time! with a great group of guides
review.reviewBody: our guides were awesome! really fun, enjoyable people to be around! the specific guide with my boat, Ian, was a really dope dude! kept the hype going all throughout the trip. really impressed with what this company does! great job guys! - danny

review.name: Friendly staff, super fun
review.reviewBody: Rafting with Ian was super fun! Definitely plan on going again next year. I recommend the skykomish river just for the Boulder drop rapid.

review.name: Good times
review.reviewBody:
Great tour by Ian, Eric and Joe.  They got us paddling well and made us part of the plan in getting through the falls.  

Tours by other operators looked more like guided Disney rides where folks did not paddle through the complex parts, but were sitting still as the other guides steered through the tough sections.  Glad we went with Triad.

review.name: Fantastic trip on Skykomish!
review.reviewBody: It was raining when we visited, which only added more fun to the tour since the drop was even higher. We had Conor as our guide, he is super professional, chill, and fun. The rest of the crew are also very helpful. They were in separate kayak/rafts to ensured our safety along the way. Half of the people on our raft are first timers but we were able to paddling through the rapids under Conor's good guidance. Will definitely come back again! :)

review.name: Safe, Fun and Adventurous
review.reviewBody: I went last Friday on June 11th and had an awesome time! It was my first time white water rafting and I felt completely safe with the guide there to lead us through it and direct us! I highly recommend them for all your white water rafting adventures in the area! If you get a chance have Ian Harkins as your guide, he was informative, knowledgeable and fun!

itemListElement.name: Scenic Landscapes Northwest Geology - Ice Age Floods Tour

name: Scenic Landscapes Northwest Geology - Ice Age Floods Tour
description: This tour, with it's terrain, will stun you. Desert, sagebrush, mountains, plateaus, wheat fields, apple orchards, and a landscape of gouged-out earth is incredible to see.  Lakes, the left overs of former massive flooding, are in some coulees. 12 hours total for the day, you'll love this tour. Non BPA Souvenir water bottle and snacks included. Yes, we stop for lunch and snacks and stretches and photo opportunities.

review.name: See the past of our planet on this tour
review.reviewBody:
If you love to be wow'd by the grandeur, beauty and immensity of our planet's past, this is the tour for you. The 400 mile trip views over 200 million years of geology from the  beautiful mountain scenery formed millions of years ago by colliding tectonic plates with igneus beginnings deep within the earth, to the present view of a mountain pasture, which happened to be  hosting a herd of elk. This wonderful odyssey takes you from the Puget Lowlands, through parts of both the North and South Cascades, across the verdant agriculture fields on the loess covered prairie of  the Columbia basin to the bottom of giant canyons carved out by a hard-to-fathom series of immense floods during the ice ages.     

This was a great tour and Cheryl was a fantastic tour guide.

review.name: A Wonderful, Informative and Fun Tour
review.reviewBody:
The tour was super interesting, and Cheryl (we got the head honcho herself!) was fun and knowledgeable throughout. Me and my wife really enjoyed the unique style of the tour that had us learning about many interesting things. Not just at the flood area either, but both on the way there and the way back.

The tour is structured in a loose way, taking a lot of cues from the customers and what you want to do. Want to make a stop somewhere? Just let them know! Want to get food? Just mention it! Want to get out of the car and walk into a snowy field and just take in the sights for a while? Totally go for it! Me and my wife really appreciated the tailored nature of the trip, and enjoyed the smaller and more intimate style much more than the large bus tours other companies tend toward.

name: Small-Group Tour: Seattle City Highlights
description: Small group tours of Seattle. Drive by sightseeing the Space Needle, Pike Place Market and all major attractions, highlights and picture postcard photo-ops on a three hour tour in comfortable motor coaches with tours of never more than 14 guests. Fun, entertaining and informative guides provide local flavor with personal anecdotes and historical nuggets only a local could know.

review.name: The Best Tour Guide
review.reviewBody: When we booked this tour we were told our Guide was the best they had and they were 100 percent correct.James Grindle our Tour Guide was Awesome.He was extremely knowledgeable and really knows Seattle and shared a lot of very interesting facts.We had a wonderful afternoon touring and learning about Seattle.Thanks again James for the Great tour July 4th

review.name: Excellent Overview of the Seattle Area
review.reviewBody: This was a great tour.  The bus was comfortable and the driver/guide was informative and entertaining.  Our tour guide, Lucky, provided a lot of information in an easy to listen to presentation.  Our favorite parts were the locks, fish ladder and “Fraiser View”.  We were only in Seattle for two days and this tour was a good use of our time.  We would recommend it to you.
